Clean and debeard the mussels. If any mussels are opened, tap them lightly on a hard surface. If they don't close, discard them.Heat the olive oil in a wide, heavy-based pan. Add the shallots and garlic and cook until softened, but not browned.Add the wine to the pan and boil for a minute to burn off the alcohol.Add the mussels to the pan. Add most of the chopped parsley, cover the pan with a lid and cook the mussels for about 3-4 minutes, giving the pan a shake from time to time. The mussels are cooked when they've opened up. Be sure to discard any that don't open.Sprinkle in the remaining parsley, then spoon the mussels into a serving bowl. Pour over the cooking liquid and serve with some crusty bread.